posts.title: Sold my parent's home to two young people, and NOT Blackrock, et-al.
posts.content: Lost my dad in 2021 and mom back in April. We got an offer for $25k more from an investment company, but this young couple made an offer for a little under asking, and we accepted their offer. They're the type of people my parents would want there. My mom and dad lived there for 53 years, and were the only owners. They had 60 years of marriage. God speed to this young couple, and we wish them decades of love and prosperity.
